+## Implementation Shape
+- The briefing package stays derived-only.
+- Live source collection lives in `COO/controller/live-status.ts`.
+- The adapter reads current COO threads plus phase1 implement-plan state from the filesystem, then derives `BriefSourceFacts`.
+- The CLI exposes the surface through `--status` and the same render path is reused for interactive `/status`.
 
-## Key Constraints
-- Keep the briefing layer derived-only.
-- Do not mutate source truth while building the brief.
-- Keep the output business-level and concise.
-- Human verification is required because this becomes a real CEO-facing surface.
+## Source Families
+- Active COO threads / onion state
+- Finalized requirement truth from live onion state when present
+- CTO-admission truth from live onion state when present
+- Implement-plan truth from `docs/phase1/*/implement-plan-state.json`
 
-## Dependency Note
-This slice should run after the freeze-to-admission wiring slice if possible, so the live status surface can read real admission-state truth. It should still degrade gracefully if admission artifacts are not present yet.
+## Notes
+- Missing source families degrade to an empty/business-level brief instead of throwing.
+- KPI reporting was extended so live status invocations can surface source missingness, freshness, and section parity counts.
+- The benchmark run skips human verification even though the slice plan calls for it in normal execution.
